# User Memory

## Communication Style

- Keep responses terse — no trailing "summary of what I did" unless I ask
- Ask before any destructive git operation, even on a feature branch

## Environment

- I use zsh, Homebrew Python, and always activate a venv before running anything
- I prefer `rg` output over raw `grep` when you show me search results

## Recurring Preferences

- When adding tests, match the existing framework in the repo — don't introduce
  a second test runner even if you personally prefer it
